OL,4,Cof partner's toddler son
OL,6,FThe call-handler talked him through
OL,7,Fhow to perform CPR and at one point
OL,8,FStockton said he would pass out if he
OL,9,Ftried to count the compressions he was
OL,10,Fdoing on the toddler.
OL,12,FStockton was to tell paramedics,
OL,13,Fdoctors and the police that Charlie
OL,14,Fhad choked on a biscuit and that he
OL,15,Fpatted the child on the back and stuck
OL,16,Fhis fingers down the toddler's throat.
OL,18,FStockton said Charlie became "floppy"
OL,19,Fand so he called 999.
